    "rationale": "All 13 V&V 40 credibility factors assessed. Twelve of thirteen factors meet or exceed required levels. One factor (Test conditions) achieved level 2 against required level 3 due to single ASTM F1717 test condition; the assessment team accepted this gap given established regulatory precedent for single-condition F1717 submissions and the Medium model risk level. All three QoIs pass the E/uval < 1.96 quantitative acceptance criterion. Overall credibility is sufficient to support a Medium assurance level decision for the non-cannulated 7.5 mm pedicle screw compression-bending COU.",
